<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-04-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-04-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="359" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d359">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Porter</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy
                                        of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-04-16"><hi rend="italic">April 16,
                                1903</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Porter reports that war vessels of four nations went to Algiers and
                            saluted the President of France on his arrival there on April 15; that
                            the President, in returning from an important official visit to Tunis,
                            will arrive at Marseille on April 30. Ambassador suggests that United
                            States war ships should go to Marseille and salute the President on his
                            arrival.)</p>
                    </div>
